      "name": "Mesh independence study — NIH convergence across three refinement levels",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) analysis performed across coarse (1.2M), medium (3.8M), and fine (9.1M) cell meshes. GCI for NIH between medium and fine meshes is 2.3%, below the 5% threshold required at MRL 2. Richardson extrapolation confirms monotonic convergence.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-geometry-dataset"
